  "spiritual_impact": "Passions arise from Mohniya Karma. They taint our intellect, create new karma, and prevent spiritual progress. Conquering attachment (Rag) is the key to overcoming all passions.",
  "summary": "This article explains that the four main passions — Anger (Krodha), Ego (Maan), Deceit (Maya), and Greed (Lobha) — are the greatest obstacles
to spiritual liberation in Jainism. These passions are further divided by intensity and are supported by nine pseudo-passions. The article emphasizes
that passions keep the soul trapped in the cycle of birth and death, and conquering them (especially attachment) is essential for attaining Moksha. Staying calm 
and detached during difficult situations helps stop the inflow of new karma."
